00:54:31.160 --> 00:54:34.080
Hit me with your best shot,
your most powerful spell.

761
00:54:34.160 --> 00:54:35.200
Okay.

762
00:54:35.280 --> 00:54:37.440
Get the ring out.
Put it on. Good boy.

763
00:54:40.000 --> 00:54:41.120
Okay.

764
00:54:42.080 --> 00:54:43.200
Ow!

765
00:54:43.280 --> 00:54:45.040
No, I'm joking.
Nothing is happening.

766
00:54:45.120 --> 00:54:47.000
Have you cleared
your mind?
Yeah, I'm pretty sure.

767
00:54:47.080 --> 00:54:49.040
That's nerves and
it's the pressure.
I got nothing happening.

768
00:54:49.120 --> 00:54:51.120
I'm new at this.
The ring's on.
Take the ring off.

769
00:54:51.200 --> 00:54:52.240
Take off the ring.
Take it off.

770
00:54:52.320 --> 00:54:53.560
Yeah, it doesn't
help me...

771
00:54:53.640 --> 00:54:55.960
Enough, you idiot.
Watch the door.

772
00:55:00.560 --> 00:55:02.040
You.

773
00:55:05.360 --> 00:55:06.440
No!

774
00:55:08.400 --> 00:55:09.680
Hello, Dave.

775
00:55:09.760 --> 00:55:10.800
Hi.

776
00:55:11.840 --> 00:55:13.200
So, Dave.

777
00:55:13.280 --> 00:55:14.320
Oh, man.

778
00:55:16.520 --> 00:55:17.840
I'm going to kill you.

779
00:55:17.920 --> 00:55:21.080
Oh, yes, right here
in this dismal bathroom.

780
00:55:21.160 --> 00:55:23.840
It's not very classy,
but there you go.

781
00:55:24.600 --> 00:55:26.240
But before we get to
that unpleasantness,

782
00:55:26.320 --> 00:55:28.280
you're going to tell me
where the Grimhold is.

783
00:55:29.960 --> 00:55:31.000
Where is she?

784
00:55:32.560 --> 00:55:33.640
She?

785
00:55:35.760 --> 00:55:37.840
He hasn't told you,
has he?

786
00:55:38.680 --> 00:55:41.360
The truth about
who's inside the doll?

787
00:55:43.360 --> 00:55:47.520
Sweetheart,
you've put your faith
in the wrong man.

788
00:55:49.680 --> 00:55:53.160
Tell me,
have you ever
been in love?

789
00:55:54.800 --> 00:55:55.800
I...
Yeah.

790
00:55:55.880 --> 00:55:58.280
You're in love right now.
I can see it in your eyes.

791
00:55:58.360 --> 00:56:00.560
No, no, no, no.
Don't deny it.

792
00:56:02.040 --> 00:56:03.360
I wonder
what would happen

793
00:56:05.040 --> 00:56:06.600
if you lost her.

794
00:56:08.320 --> 00:56:09.680
Shut up.

795
00:56:12.960 --> 00:56:15.680
You'd be no better
than the rest of us.

796
00:56:23.200 --> 00:56:24.560
Where is the Grimhold?

797
00:56:27.560 --> 00:56:28.560
I don't know.

798
00:56:29.120 --> 00:56:31.920
Oh, Dave, you really are
the most dreadful liar.

799
00:56:32.000 --> 00:56:34.200
That's what I keep
telling him.

800
00:56:34.280 --> 00:56:35.680
Want your guy back?

801
00:56:38.000 --> 00:56:38.960
Oh!

802
00:56:43.080 --> 00:56:46.720
It's been a while
since I've seen the
Hungarian Mirror Trap.

803
00:56:50.760 --> 00:56:52.200
I guess I'm just
old-fashioned.

804
00:56:57.760 --> 00:56:59.520
Balthazar, look out!

805
00:57:05.720 --> 00:57:07.920
What are you
doing here, Dave?

806
00:57:08.760 --> 00:57:10.520
Horvath was
trying to kill me.

807
00:57:10.600 --> 00:57:13.000
His moral compass
doesn't exactly
point north.

808
00:57:13.120 --> 00:57:15.200
Yeah, well,
what about yours? Huh?

809
00:57:15.520 --> 00:57:18.320
You haven't been
completely truthful
with me.

810
00:57:19.080 --> 00:57:21.160
That guy called me
the Prime Merlinean.

811
00:57:21.480 --> 00:57:23.440
Balthazar,
what is that?

812
00:57:23.680 --> 00:57:25.720
Now, I'm not doing
anything else

813
00:57:26.040 --> 00:57:29.840
until you start
being truthful with me
about what's going on.

814
00:57:31.680 --> 00:57:33.680
Who is in that Grimhold?

815
00:57:35.600 --> 00:57:36.800
Morgana.

816
00:57:44.120 --> 00:57:45.440
Wake up that moron

817
00:57:45.520 --> 00:57:48.200
in stall number three
for me, would you?

818
00:57:53.640 --> 00:57:54.960
Oh, for heaven's sake.

819
00:57:56.760 --> 00:57:57.960
BALTHAZAR: Morgana.

820
00:57:58.440 --> 00:58:02.320
She was making
preparations
for The Rising,

821
00:58:02.960 --> 00:58:05.640
something that
would enable her
to enslave mankind

822
00:58:05.720 --> 00:58:08.240
by resurrecting
dead Morganian sorcerers.

823
00:58:09.200 --> 00:58:11.400
So, after the witch girl,
there's another doll

824
00:58:11.480 --> 00:58:13.880
that contains
the greatest evil
the world has ever known?

825
00:58:14.240 --> 00:58:15.280
She's in the last doll.

826
00:58:15.680 --> 00:58:19.400
And what does it
have to do with this

827
00:58:20.840 --> 00:58:22.560
Prime Merlinean?

828
00:58:22.640 --> 00:58:24.640
Merlin had
three apprentices.

829
00:58:25.080 --> 00:58:26.280
I was one of them.

830
00:58:27.720 --> 00:58:30.080
You were
Merlin's apprentice?

831
00:58:30.360 --> 00:58:32.240
He cast a spell to
keep us from aging

832
00:58:32.640 --> 00:58:36.160
until we found the sorcerer
who would inherit his power.

833
00:58:37.520 --> 00:58:39.320
And his dragon ring.

834
00:58:42.120 --> 00:58:45.120
Some part of you,
no matter how small,

835
00:58:46.640 --> 00:58:48.320
must share the same blood.

836
00:58:49.760 --> 00:58:51.440
As Merlin?

837
00:58:51.760 --> 00:58:53.560
Great men have
always been called.

838
00:58:53.880 --> 00:58:55.680
This is your calling.

839
00:58:57.160 --> 00:58:58.200
Merlin said,

840
00:58:58.960 --> 00:59:03.120
"The only one who will
ever be able to destroy
Morgana once and for all

841
00:59:03.200 --> 00:59:04.840
"is the Prime Merlinean."

842
00:59:06.680 --> 00:59:09.080
So I'm supposed
to save the world.

843
00:59:10.760 --> 00:59:13.960
I... I just don't think
I'm up for that.

844
00:59:15.280 --> 00:59:17.120
Do you think I've been
teaching you magic tricks

845
00:59:17.240 --> 00:59:18.800
for some little
girl's tea party?

846
00:59:20.880 --> 00:59:23.120
When you stepped
inside this circle,

847
00:59:23.200 --> 00:59:25.320
I told you there
was no going back.

848
00:59:25.400 --> 00:59:26.480
You took an oath!

849
00:59:28.200 --> 00:59:31.240
I have been searching
1,000 years for you.

850
00:59:31.960 --> 00:59:34.600
Fighting Morganians,
protecting the Grimhold.

851
00:59:34.720 --> 00:59:36.480
You're going to
set me free.

852
00:59:37.200 --> 00:59:39.240
You have to become
the Prime Merlinean.

853
00:59:40.160 --> 00:59:41.920
And I'm not asking.

854
00:59:50.640 --> 00:59:53.640
I have a student
who's failing my class.
I need his file.

855
00:59:54.520 --> 00:59:58.000
First I'll need to see your
faculty identification card.

856
00:59:59.440 --> 01:00:04.080
You don't need
to see my faculty
identification card.

857
01:00:07.920 --> 01:00:11.000
I don't need your
faculty identification card.

858
01:00:11.920 --> 01:00:14.880
"These are not the droids
you're looking for."

859
01:00:14.960 --> 01:00:16.280
(LAUGHING)

860
01:00:20.280 --> 01:00:24.680
Here it is. He has
an unauthorized lab space.

861
01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:27.560
(GROANING)

862
01:00:27.640 --> 01:00:31.800
Okay, so, how will
I know when I'm it?

863
01:00:32.440 --> 01:00:34.920
The Prime Merlinean?

864
01:00:35.360 --> 01:00:38.800
The Prime Merlinean
will become
so powerful within

865
01:00:39.680 --> 01:00:41.960
he no longer
needs his ring
to cast magic.

866
01:00:42.480 --> 01:00:43.880
When you can do that,

867
01:00:44.320 --> 01:00:46.120
you're ready to
take on Morgana.

868
01:00:48.320 --> 01:00:50.800
Tank! What is he
doing here anyway?

869
01:00:53.200 --> 01:00:55.000
This should be good.

870
01:00:56.600 --> 01:00:58.840
Schematic for
a fusion spell.

871
01:00:59.520 --> 01:01:02.640
The merging of two souls
into one physical body.

872
01:01:03.120 --> 01:01:05.840
I've only ever
seen one sorcerer

873
01:01:05.920 --> 01:01:07.760
successfully pull
off human fusion.

874
01:01:08.080 --> 01:01:10.520
And Tank is here for...

875
01:01:10.760 --> 01:01:11.840
Practice.

876
01:01:12.040 --> 01:01:15.000
Are you telling me
you're trying to
possess Tank?

877
01:01:18.480 --> 01:01:20.400
(FARTING)

878
01:01:20.480 --> 01:01:23.680
Yeah. I'm not
so sure it's the
best idea, either.

879
01:01:24.280 --> 01:01:25.440
No.

880
01:01:28.560 --> 01:01:29.680
Oh, man.

881
01:01:31.920 --> 01:01:36.240
Becky's coming now,
and I'm standing
in a puddle of pop.

882
01:01:36.320 --> 01:01:37.560
I need to stop and clean.

883
01:01:37.680 --> 01:01:38.920
We're not
done training.

884
01:01:39.000 --> 01:01:40.080
(EXHALING)

885
01:01:40.160 --> 01:01:45.040
Balthazar, I've been
waiting for 10 years
to see this girl again.

886
01:01:45.760 --> 01:01:47.760
Do you have any idea
what that's like?

887
01:01:50.360 --> 01:01:52.040
When I come back,
you better be focused.

888
01:01:56.720 --> 01:01:57.720
Ow.

889
01:02:00.440 --> 01:02:02.240
This is really sticky.

890
01:02:05.040 --> 01:02:06.400
I'm doomed.

891
01:02:08.480 --> 01:02:09.560
This.

892
01:02:13.360 --> 01:02:15.160
Thank you.
Thank you.

893
01:03:47.800 --> 01:03:49.680
I command you to stop!

894
01:03:54.920 --> 01:03:56.800
Oh, no. Man.

895
01:04:03.840 --> 01:04:05.480
(EXCLAIMING)

896
01:04:09.840 --> 01:04:11.360
(EXCLAIMING)

897
01:04:22.680 --> 01:04:24.240
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

898
01:04:25.240 --> 01:04:26.280
Becky.

899
01:04:27.200 --> 01:04:28.200
Hi.

900
01:04:28.280 --> 01:04:30.040
Hi. You're on time.

901
01:04:30.760 --> 01:04:32.120
You forgot?

902
01:04:32.200 --> 01:04:34.880
No, no, no.
I didn't forget.

903
01:04:35.160 --> 01:04:36.920
Is everything okay?
What, me?

904
01:04:37.000 --> 01:04:38.680
How are you doing?
(EXCLAIMING)

905
01:04:38.840 --> 01:04:40.720
I'm good. I'm good.

906
01:04:40.800 --> 01:04:43.960
Would you please stop that?
Will you...

907
01:04:44.040 --> 01:04:45.040
(EXCLAIMS)

908
01:04:47.600 --> 01:04:50.160
It's probably best
for you to leave.

909
01:04:50.720 --> 01:04:52.200
What am I saying?

910
01:04:52.280 --> 01:04:54.560
Okay. Okay, I will go.

911
01:04:54.920 --> 01:04:57.480
Yeah, I'm sorry.
I'm having issues.

912
01:05:05.600 --> 01:05:06.720
My coils!

913
01:05:14.960 --> 01:05:16.160
(EXCLAIMING)

914
01:05:20.760 --> 01:05:21.880
Disperse!

915
01:05:34.160 --> 01:05:36.400
You have abused
the sacred art,

916
01:05:37.280 --> 01:05:39.440
and you have abused
the Merlin Circle.

917
01:05:39.760 --> 01:05:41.280
Magic isn't a game.

918
01:05:41.600 --> 01:05:42.960
No shortcuts!

919
01:05:43.280 --> 01:05:45.680
Falling in that water
and getting electrocuted,

920
01:05:45.760 --> 01:05:47.560
that's how a sorcerer
loses his power!

921
01:05:47.640 --> 01:05:51.680
What rule is that?
Fourteen? Twenty-seven?

922
01:05:51.760 --> 01:05:53.000
I can't even remember!

923
01:05:53.080 --> 01:05:54.400
What difference
does it make

924
01:05:54.480 --> 01:05:56.800
if it's obvious
that I can't even
control a few mops?

925
01:05:56.880 --> 01:05:58.800
The stronger the man,
the stronger the sorcerer.

926
01:05:58.880 --> 01:06:01.080
Thank you. Thank you
for another useless motto!

927
01:06:01.160 --> 01:06:02.480
I have another one for you.

928
01:06:02.560 --> 01:06:05.240
You will not control
your magic if you will
not control yourself.

929
01:06:05.360 --> 01:06:07.960
You need to stop your
worrying and start
believing in yourself.

930
01:06:08.320 --> 01:06:09.440
Is that what you do?

931
01:06:09.520 --> 01:06:11.080
What I do
isn't the point.

932
01:06:11.200 --> 01:06:12.240
I think it is.

933
01:06:12.320 --> 01:06:16.080
I'm convinced you exist
purely to make my life
a living hell.

934
01:06:18.880 --> 01:06:21.440
You don't know anything
about a living hell.

935
01:06:27.160 --> 01:06:28.200
You're making progress.

936
01:06:28.280 --> 01:06:30.160
No, I'm not
making progress.

937
01:06:32.400 --> 01:06:33.960
No ring, right?

938
01:06:38.080 --> 01:06:41.240
No magic.
I can't move the chairs.
I can't do it.

939
01:06:43.640 --> 01:06:45.240
It's not me, Balthazar.

940
01:06:45.320 --> 01:06:47.360
I'm sorry!
I'm sorry.

941
01:06:49.040 --> 01:06:50.720
I'm not it.

942
01:06:51.120 --> 01:06:54.480
I'm not a hero.
I'm not the
Prime Merlinean.

943
01:06:54.640 --> 01:06:56.680
I'm just a physics nerd

944
01:06:57.200 --> 01:07:00.600
who looks really,
really stupid
in these shoes.

945
01:08:11.800 --> 01:08:12.920
Dave.

946
01:08:15.080 --> 01:08:16.800
What are you
doing here?

947
01:08:17.040 --> 01:08:20.960
I saw you outside
the coffee shop,
so I followed you.

948
01:08:21.240 --> 01:08:24.080
You looked a little more
distressed than usual.

949
01:08:24.520 --> 01:08:25.760
That bad, huh?

950
01:08:26.280 --> 01:08:28.320
Did you really think
that one botched date

951
01:08:28.400 --> 01:08:30.600
was going to make me
hate you forever?

952
01:08:32.760 --> 01:08:33.880
Yeah.

953
01:08:35.760 --> 01:08:39.680
I do have to ask you
this one thing.

954
01:08:42.280 --> 01:08:43.360
What are you
doing up here?

955
01:08:44.440 --> 01:08:45.600
Yeah.

956
01:08:46.880 --> 01:08:49.000
A friend of mine
brought me here once.

957
01:08:49.640 --> 01:08:52.720
And the height
doesn't bother you?

958
01:08:54.040 --> 01:08:55.200
Are you afraid
of heights?

959
01:08:55.280 --> 01:08:56.480
A little bit, yeah.

960
01:08:56.760 --> 01:08:58.120
Trust me.
Here, come on.

961
01:08:58.400 --> 01:09:00.440
Come on. You're good.

962
01:09:00.720 --> 01:09:02.800
You're good.
I don't know.

963
01:09:04.440 --> 01:09:05.880
(BECKY SIGHING)

964
01:09:07.280 --> 01:09:08.360
Wow.

965
01:09:09.080 --> 01:09:11.480
Yeah. Wow.

966
01:09:14.000 --> 01:09:17.480
Do you remember
when you drew King Kong
on the bus window?

967
01:09:17.560 --> 01:09:19.960
And he lined up with
the Empire State Building?

968
01:09:21.480 --> 01:09:22.520
You remember that?

969
01:09:23.160 --> 01:09:24.560
It was cool.

970
01:09:26.840 --> 01:09:30.040
You saw the world
in your own way.

971
01:09:31.000 --> 01:09:32.560
I was just trying
to impress you.

972
01:09:34.440 --> 01:09:38.480
Well, it worked.
Not bad for
a 10-year-old kid.

973
01:09:39.800 --> 01:09:42.000
Yeah, right.
What happened?

974
01:09:43.560 --> 01:09:45.120
What? What do you mean?

975
01:09:45.200 --> 01:09:46.600
The bitter irony
of the fact

976
01:09:46.680 --> 01:09:50.400
that 10-year-old me
is far cooler
than 20-year-old me.

977
01:09:51.240 --> 01:09:54.240
I think
20-year-old Dave is...
He's all right.

978
01:09:55.040 --> 01:09:59.520
Like, "all right" all right,
or "all right!" all right?

979
01:09:59.600 --> 01:10:01.120
(LAUGHING)

980
01:10:01.200 --> 01:10:02.320
(SIGHS)

981
01:10:02.400 --> 01:10:06.080
I think he is
somewhere in the middle.

982
01:10:06.840 --> 01:10:09.680
That's a diplomatic answer.

983
01:10:10.840 --> 01:10:12.040
And thank you.

984
01:10:21.800 --> 01:10:23.560
Hey.
Hello.

985
01:10:23.800 --> 01:10:24.840
I'm sorry.

986
01:10:25.400 --> 01:10:27.680
I think you and I
need to have a talk.

987
01:10:28.280 --> 01:10:31.240
No apology necessary.
Let us move on.

988
01:10:31.800 --> 01:10:33.160
(WITH ENGLISH ACCENT)
You're a diamond, mate.

989
01:10:48.200 --> 01:10:49.680
HORVATH:
Surprisingly well done.

990
01:10:49.880 --> 01:10:51.240
Now go find
the Grimhold.

991
01:10:55.240 --> 01:10:58.440
You seem to have
rather a soft spot
for that boy.

992
01:10:58.840 --> 01:11:01.160
Has Balthazar
made a new friend?

993
01:11:02.160 --> 01:11:03.440
I don't see
the Grimhold.

994
01:11:03.520 --> 01:11:06.160
That's because
you're using your eyes.

995
01:11:06.520 --> 01:11:08.160
Clever Balthazar.

996
01:11:09.040 --> 01:11:11.040
Always up to his
little tricks.

997
01:11:33.400 --> 01:11:34.480
Found it.

998
01:11:38.120 --> 01:11:39.760
It's lighter
than I remember.

999
01:11:41.480 --> 01:11:43.280
We once fought
together, Maxim.

1000
01:11:43.400 --> 01:11:45.320
A lot's happened
since those days.

1001
01:11:45.600 --> 01:11:46.880
This isn't about that.

1002
01:11:46.960 --> 01:11:48.640
Oh, yes, it is, Balthazar.

1003
01:11:49.480 --> 01:11:50.920
It's always been
about that.

1004
01:11:51.680 --> 01:11:54.360
Veronica chose you
instead of me,

1005
01:11:54.440 --> 01:11:56.360
the great
Balthazar Blake,

1006
01:11:58.440 --> 01:12:00.000
my best friend.

1007
01:12:00.760 --> 01:12:05.040
Well, I'm going to let you
watch me release Morgana.

1008
01:12:05.360 --> 01:12:08.480
Let you watch your world
crumble into nothing!

1009
01:12:30.720 --> 01:12:32.360
HORVATH:
Drake. Let's go.

1010
01:12:35.200 --> 01:12:36.240
Nice catch.

1011
01:12:36.520 --> 01:12:37.560
I owed you one.

1012
01:12:38.120 --> 01:12:40.200
They got the doll.
Let's get it back.

1013
01:12:44.280 --> 01:12:45.520
Hang on.

1014
01:12:46.360 --> 01:12:47.480
Hang on, Tank.

1015
01:12:51.600 --> 01:12:52.680
(CAR HORNS HONKING)

1016
01:12:52.760 --> 01:12:53.760
(EXCLAIMING)

1017
01:13:02.920 --> 01:13:03.960
Go left.

1018
01:13:04.040 --> 01:13:05.840
(CAR HORNS HONKING)

1019
01:13:09.560 --> 01:13:11.440
Whoa! What the...

1020
01:13:11.520 --> 01:13:14.200
BALTHAZAR: Horvath!
He's in here somewhere.

1021
01:13:14.320 --> 01:13:16.920
Wait. He has the power to
turn his car into a taxi?

1022
01:13:17.240 --> 01:13:19.160
Use your ring
and lock in
on the Grimhold.

1023
01:13:19.240 --> 01:13:20.800
Remember,
it moves with the ring.

1024
01:13:20.880 --> 01:13:22.600
Okay, yeah.
Right, right, right.

1025
01:13:28.720 --> 01:13:30.200
(TAXI HORNS HONKING)

1026
01:13:30.280 --> 01:13:31.360
Go! Go!

1027
01:13:34.640 --> 01:13:35.680
Here they come!

1028
01:13:41.440 --> 01:13:42.480
Whoa!

1029
01:13:42.560 --> 01:13:43.600
What the heck!

1030
01:13:45.040 --> 01:13:46.880
(EXCLAIMS) Nice one!

1031
01:13:52.720 --> 01:13:54.640
Hey! Well, look at that.
Hang on.

1032
01:14:02.600 --> 01:14:03.600
Oh, my God.

1033
01:14:04.120 --> 01:14:05.200
Take the tunnel.

1034
01:14:09.000 --> 01:14:10.880
(CAR HORNS HONKING)

1035
01:14:18.480 --> 01:14:20.320
What is that, smoke?

1036
01:14:26.080 --> 01:14:27.720
Oh, come on!

1037
01:14:40.000 --> 01:14:41.640
Time for a little revenge.

1038
01:14:44.400 --> 01:14:45.400
(EXCLAIMING)

1039
01:14:49.200 --> 01:14:50.240
DAVE: What the heck
is this?

1040
01:14:50.320 --> 01:14:51.760
Yes, we drove
through a mirror.

1041
01:14:51.880 --> 01:14:53.840
We're trapped in
a reverse world.
So...

1042
01:14:53.920 --> 01:14:56.440
It is, it is.
Horvath's payback
for the bathroom mirror.

1043
01:14:56.520 --> 01:14:57.880
No, no.
We won't die as long as

1044
01:14:57.960 --> 01:14:59.400
we get out
of here soon.
Okay.

1045
01:14:59.480 --> 01:15:01.000
By driving through
our own reflection.

1046
01:15:01.080 --> 01:15:02.120
Fantastic.

1047
01:15:02.200 --> 01:15:04.000
DAVE: There.
In the window.
This is it.

1048
01:15:12.840 --> 01:15:13.840
(DAVE EXCLAIMING)

1049
01:15:13.920 --> 01:15:15.400
No, no, no, no, no.
You're not...

1050
01:15:15.680 --> 01:15:17.680
Here we go.
We're not going
to make that!

1051
01:15:18.520 --> 01:15:20.520
We're not...
(SCREAMING)

1052
01:15:37.440 --> 01:15:38.440
(SCREAMING)

1053
01:15:40.880 --> 01:15:42.080
Hello, Balthazar.

1054
01:15:43.240 --> 01:15:44.480
Oh, man. Oh, man.

1055
01:15:44.600 --> 01:15:46.200
No, no, no.
Back up. Back up.
Back up. Back up.

1056
01:15:46.280 --> 01:15:48.200
Back up. Back up.
Back up. Back up.

1057
01:15:50.400 --> 01:15:51.440
Oh, man.

1058
01:15:52.480 --> 01:15:54.080
I've got an idea.
I've got an idea.

1059
01:15:54.480 --> 01:15:56.160
Dave, don't.
Please just let me do it.

1060
01:15:58.880 --> 01:15:59.920
What?

1061
01:16:00.000 --> 01:16:01.760
'73 Pinto?
This is your idea?

1062
01:16:01.840 --> 01:16:05.560
No! No. My idea
was to turn their
car into a beater.

1063
01:16:05.680 --> 01:16:06.960
(MOANING)

1064
01:16:13.400 --> 01:16:14.560
Finish it.
Right!

1065
01:16:17.400 --> 01:16:18.400
(EXCLAIMING)

1066
01:16:24.400 --> 01:16:25.720
I think he stopped.

1067
01:16:37.280 --> 01:16:40.720
DAVE: Hold on, Tank.
Hold on, Tank.
I got you, buddy.

1068
01:16:40.840 --> 01:16:42.360
MAN: ...walked away.

1069
01:17:00.160 --> 01:17:01.240
Hey!

1070
01:17:02.400 --> 01:17:05.440
I'm sorry. I thought
you were someone else.

1071
01:17:09.280 --> 01:17:10.680
Where's Horvath?

1072
01:17:10.960 --> 01:17:12.560
Did he get away?

1073
01:17:12.640 --> 01:17:15.280
Where's the Grimhold?
Who was that?

1074
01:17:17.760 --> 01:17:19.120
That was her, wasn't it?

1075
01:17:19.840 --> 01:17:21.640
The third apprentice.

1076
01:17:25.040 --> 01:17:28.880
For centuries,
Veronica, Horvath and I
were the only thing standing

1077
01:17:28.960 --> 01:17:31.560
between Morgana
and man's destruction.

1078
01:17:32.480 --> 01:17:34.280
Our friendship
and our magic

1079
01:17:34.360 --> 01:17:36.240
were what Veronica
and I depended on.

1080
01:17:38.400 --> 01:17:39.480
You fell for her,
didn't you?

1081
01:17:42.000 --> 01:17:43.520
I fell for her.

1082
01:17:46.400 --> 01:17:49.520
<i>Like you, all Veronica</i>
<i>wanted was to be normal.</i>

1083
01:17:50.560 --> 01:17:53.520
<i>Normal things,</i>
<i>normal life.</i>

1084
01:17:55.680 --> 01:17:56.880
<i>I fell.</i>

1085
01:17:59.840 --> 01:18:01.280
And so did Horvath.

1086
01:18:03.720 --> 01:18:05.840
That's why Horvath
betrayed us.

1087
01:18:06.240 --> 01:18:08.160
For 1,000 years,

1088
01:18:08.240 --> 01:18:10.520
you've been carrying her
around with you.

1089
01:18:10.960 --> 01:18:12.520
In the Grimhold.

1090
01:18:13.920 --> 01:18:16.720
I was going to
give this to her
that night.

1091
01:18:25.360 --> 01:18:26.720
I'm sorry.

1092
01:18:30.080 --> 01:18:31.440
Okay, Balthazar.

1093
01:18:31.800 --> 01:18:36.160
We are going to
get Veronica out
and destroy Morgana.

1094
01:18:38.320 --> 01:18:39.720
What's happened to you?

1095
01:18:40.160 --> 01:18:41.200
Nothing.

1096
01:18:41.520 --> 01:18:42.920
You're still
a bad liar.

1097
01:18:43.440 --> 01:18:44.480
Why does everyone...

1098
01:18:44.560 --> 01:18:46.960
You know,
I am glad she likes you.

1099
01:18:47.040 --> 01:18:50.160
No, I am not surprised.
Only glad.

1100
01:18:51.080 --> 01:18:53.520
There's nothing
like it, is there?

1101
01:18:55.720 --> 01:18:59.520
Put your old man
shoes back on.

1102
01:19:00.480 --> 01:19:01.560
We have some work to do.

1103
01:19:06.000 --> 01:19:07.400
HORVATH: Are all
the satellite dishes
in position?

1104
01:19:07.480 --> 01:19:08.560
All lined up.

1105
01:19:09.000 --> 01:19:12.000
I chipped my mani,
which is not cool.

1106
01:19:12.080 --> 01:19:13.960
No, I imagine it's not.

1107
01:19:14.760 --> 01:19:18.120
Inside there lies
our next coworker.

1108
01:19:18.520 --> 01:19:22.560
Abigail Williams,
a little witch who
put Salem on the map.

1109
01:19:23.280 --> 01:19:25.800
Once she's out,
we're at the
Morgana shell.

1110
01:19:25.880 --> 01:19:29.520
Now that's going to
take a lot of time
and energy to crack.

1111
01:19:29.600 --> 01:19:31.120
So what are we
going to do?

1112
01:19:31.200 --> 01:19:33.400
Have you heard of
the Parasite Spell?

1113
01:19:33.760 --> 01:19:35.120
(CHUCKLING)

1114
01:19:35.200 --> 01:19:38.880
Sorry, I forgot
your education's
somewhat lacking.

1115
01:19:38.960 --> 01:19:41.360
Yeah, I prefer to go
more by instinct.

1116
01:19:41.440 --> 01:19:43.320
You know,
what feels right.

1117
01:19:43.480 --> 01:19:45.920
Very good. Well,
the Parasite Spell

1118
01:19:46.000 --> 01:19:47.840
is a rather nasty
piece of business.

1119
01:19:48.360 --> 01:19:51.760
It originated in Haiti,
if memory serves.

1120
01:19:52.280 --> 01:19:56.320
It enables one sorcerer
to steal the energy
from another.

1121
01:19:57.800 --> 01:19:59.840
(GROANING)

1122
01:20:01.680 --> 01:20:04.480
Well, you weren't
really using it,
were you?

1123
01:20:11.800 --> 01:20:13.560
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

1124
01:20:15.640 --> 01:20:16.880
Excuse me?

1125
01:20:17.120 --> 01:20:18.600
I'd like to
make a request.

1126
01:20:19.200 --> 01:20:22.480
<i>I just finished my show.</i>
<i>But maybe next time, okay?</i>

1127
01:20:31.200 --> 01:20:33.680
I said I'd like
to make a request.

1128
01:20:38.680 --> 01:20:39.680
BALTHAZAR: All right.

1129
01:20:41.360 --> 01:20:45.000
When Morgana is released,
no matter what happens,

1130
01:20:45.840 --> 01:20:49.320
promise me you'll do
whatever it takes
to destroy her.

1131
01:20:51.000 --> 01:20:52.000
I promise.

1132
01:20:53.640 --> 01:20:56.520
And for the record,
you wear the old
guy shoes very well.

1133
01:20:57.680 --> 01:20:59.480
My feet
disagree with you,
but thank you.

1134
01:21:01.360 --> 01:21:02.400
Knuckle bump.

1135
01:21:05.880 --> 01:21:07.080
Might as well.

1136
01:21:08.560 --> 01:21:10.840
Now that I have
kidnapped the girl
for you,

1137
01:21:10.920 --> 01:21:13.120
is it time to
release Morgana?

1138
01:21:13.200 --> 01:21:15.320
I'll give her
your regards.

1139
01:21:16.240 --> 01:21:18.960
Mr. Horvath,
have I done
something wrong?

1140
01:21:19.040 --> 01:21:20.760
(CRACKLING)

1141
01:21:20.840 --> 01:21:21.880
HORVATH: Not at all.

1142
01:21:22.160 --> 01:21:27.880
I need your power
to free Morgana.
I just don't need you.

1143
01:21:29.320 --> 01:21:30.920
Well, that's two.

1144
01:21:31.720 --> 01:21:32.800
One more to go.

1145
01:21:43.960 --> 01:21:45.880
That's horrifying.

1146
01:21:45.960 --> 01:21:49.120
Let's just find
the Grimhold and
be done with it.

1147
01:22:02.720 --> 01:22:05.400
Battery Park.
The Rising.

1148
01:22:13.880 --> 01:22:15.120
Persian Quickrug.

1149
01:22:16.080 --> 01:22:18.080
And he thinks
I'm old-fashioned.

1150
01:22:21.720 --> 01:22:23.200
Ostentatious.

1151
01:22:33.120 --> 01:22:36.560
Ooh... Uh-huh.

1152
01:22:44.280 --> 01:22:45.920
Nothing, nothing.

1153
01:22:48.920 --> 01:22:50.600
So that's Morgana.

1154
01:22:54.560 --> 01:22:55.800
Veronica.

1155
01:23:08.040 --> 01:23:09.360
(WHISPERING) Balthazar?

1156
01:23:09.840 --> 01:23:13.000
That was easy.
Come on, Dave.
You know the drill.

1157
01:23:13.200 --> 01:23:14.800
Give me what I want,
and I'll let her go.

1158
01:23:14.880 --> 01:23:16.520
Dave, what is going on?

1159
01:23:16.640 --> 01:23:17.920
It's gonna be okay.
You're gonna be okay.

1160
01:23:18.000 --> 01:23:19.000
HORVATH: No, she's not!

1161
01:23:20.000 --> 01:23:23.120
She's going to be
ground up into chunks
and fed to the cat

1162
01:23:23.200 --> 01:23:26.320
unless you give me
Merlin's ring
and the Grimhold.

1163
01:23:26.400 --> 01:23:29.440
Balthazar? He's busy
admiring the decor.

1164
01:23:29.520 --> 01:23:31.280
So what's it
going to be?

1165
01:23:51.200 --> 01:23:52.280
(EXHALING)

1166
01:24:00.760 --> 01:24:01.880
Here.

1167
01:24:03.760 --> 01:24:04.840
Take it.

1168
01:24:09.960 --> 01:24:11.920
You're okay?
Merlin's ring.

1169
01:24:12.480 --> 01:24:15.440
It's been a while
since I've been
this close to it.

1170
01:24:16.240 --> 01:24:17.720
I wonder if
it still works.

1171
01:24:23.680 --> 01:24:24.720
You all right?

1172
01:24:24.800 --> 01:24:26.240
Yeah, I think so.

1173
01:24:32.880 --> 01:24:33.920
The Grimhold?

1174
01:24:37.920 --> 01:24:39.080
I see.

1175
01:24:40.280 --> 01:24:42.360
He took my ring.

1176
01:24:43.280 --> 01:24:45.240
He was gonna kill Becky.

1177
01:24:46.240 --> 01:24:48.240
I'm so sorry, Balthazar.

1178
01:24:49.240 --> 01:24:51.680
I would have done
the same thing, Dave.

1179
01:24:55.720 --> 01:24:56.880
Where are you going?

1180
01:24:56.960 --> 01:24:59.840
Battery Park.
Horvath's going
to release Morgana.

1181
01:24:59.920 --> 01:25:03.760
Well, you can't
take him on and Morgana
at the same time. That's...

1182
01:25:03.840 --> 01:25:05.040
You literally can't.

1183
01:25:05.120 --> 01:25:06.480
I have to try.

1184
01:25:06.560 --> 01:25:08.120
Well, then
I'm going with you.

1185
01:25:08.640 --> 01:25:10.120
Without any magic?

1186
01:25:10.520 --> 01:25:12.160
He has your ring.

1187
01:25:12.280 --> 01:25:13.440
I'm going alone.

1188
01:25:14.720 --> 01:25:15.880
(BECKY EXCLAIMS)

1189
01:25:15.960 --> 01:25:18.400
DAVE: No, that's
a normal thing for him.

1190
01:25:21.400 --> 01:25:23.920
No one knows how much
time they have

1191
01:25:25.120 --> 01:25:27.960
to be with
the people that are
the most important.

1192
01:25:28.800 --> 01:25:30.040
Enjoy it.

1193
01:25:34.240 --> 01:25:35.360
(SHRIEKING)

1194
01:25:43.960 --> 01:25:46.320
That guy just flew
away on an eagle!

1195
01:25:46.400 --> 01:25:47.880
I...
A steel eagle.

1196
01:25:48.000 --> 01:25:49.560
Becky, I wanted to talk
to you about this.

1197
01:25:49.640 --> 01:25:52.000
I just haven't known
where to start.

1198
01:25:53.200 --> 01:25:55.080
I'm just happy
you're okay.

1199
01:25:55.920 --> 01:26:00.520
Look, Dave.
If you can just
tell me the truth,

1200
01:26:00.920 --> 01:26:04.480
then I promise
I will do my best
to understand.

1201
01:26:06.160 --> 01:26:10.320
Okay. The first thing
you should know about me
is that I'm a sorcerer.

1202
01:26:13.200 --> 01:26:14.320
Okay.

1203
01:26:14.440 --> 01:26:18.760
I can conjure and
shoot plasma bolts
out of my hand.

1204
01:26:19.480 --> 01:26:21.680
I can speed time up,
slow it down,

1205
01:26:21.960 --> 01:26:26.200
varying degrees
of levitation.
It's all very magical.

1206
01:26:27.920 --> 01:26:32.160
And I thought my last
boyfriend was different
'cause he wore a scarf.

1207
01:26:33.400 --> 01:26:35.320
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)

1208
01:26:35.840 --> 01:26:37.200
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1209
01:26:37.400 --> 01:26:40.880
Baby, I'll just
come back.

1210
01:26:40.960 --> 01:26:41.960
Okay?
Okay.

1211
01:26:42.040 --> 01:26:45.520
I'll see you
in a minute.
Okay. All right. I'm here.

1212
01:26:49.400 --> 01:26:50.640
Bad time, Dave.

1213
01:26:51.040 --> 01:26:52.480
Bennet.
Thank God you answered.

1214
01:26:52.640 --> 01:26:54.040
<i>I got a real emergency</i>
<i>on my hands.</i>

1215
01:26:54.120 --> 01:26:56.920
<i>I need you to meet me</i>
<i>at my lab right now!</i>

1216
01:26:58.440 --> 01:27:00.240
Becky, I got to let you out.

1217
01:27:00.320 --> 01:27:01.720
What? Let me out?

1218
01:27:02.320 --> 01:27:03.360
Okay.

1219
01:27:03.440 --> 01:27:06.480
I think I know
how to defeat them
without any magic.

1220
01:27:06.560 --> 01:27:07.920
How?

1221
01:27:08.000 --> 01:27:09.840
The rings on
Horvath's cane.

1222
01:27:09.920 --> 01:27:11.480
He put them there
to gain more power,

1223
01:27:11.560 --> 01:27:13.400
but they make him
a better conductor.

1224
01:27:13.480 --> 01:27:16.880
Dave, I have no idea
what you're talking about.

1225
01:27:17.680 --> 01:27:20.000
All right, Rebecca,
here it is.

1226
01:27:20.920 --> 01:27:24.280
Many evil sorcerers
will be raised from
the dead tonight.

1227
01:27:24.560 --> 01:27:28.920
So, basically, Morgana
is trying to destroy
the world as we know it.

1228
01:27:30.040 --> 01:27:31.360
Oh, just that.

1229
01:27:31.920 --> 01:27:35.200
This is really dangerous.
I can't bring you into it.

1230
01:27:36.320 --> 01:27:38.400
Well, I think
I'm already into it.

1231
01:27:39.240 --> 01:27:42.960
And besides,
if you blow it, we're all
gonna die anyway, right?

1232
01:27:43.840 --> 01:27:45.360
I want to come with you.

1233
01:27:47.480 --> 01:27:48.600
You're sexy.

1234
01:27:51.400 --> 01:27:52.880
I got all the
Tesla coil remotes.

1235
01:27:52.960 --> 01:27:54.720
Thanks, brother.
I appreciate it.

1236
01:27:55.120 --> 01:27:57.280
Oh! I found this
after we hung up.

1237
01:27:58.320 --> 01:28:00.080
It was on the desk.

1238
01:28:01.280 --> 01:28:03.240
"Give this to Veronica.
Balthazar."

1239
01:28:10.080 --> 01:28:13.280
I don't think
Balthazar's planning
on coming back.

1240
01:28:15.240 --> 01:28:17.960
I don't know what
you're into here, Dave,

1241
01:28:18.400 --> 01:28:22.880
but whatever it is,
you are definitely
participating!

1242
01:28:23.800 --> 01:28:26.640
Thank you, Bennet.
I appreciate that.
We should go.

1243
01:28:40.040 --> 01:28:41.680
HORVATH:
Now is The Rising.

1244
01:28:44.120 --> 01:28:45.160
Now is the time.

1245
01:29:14.520 --> 01:29:15.760
Veronica.

1246
01:29:18.680 --> 01:29:21.200
It's me, Horvath.
Morgana.

1247
01:29:22.280 --> 01:29:24.400
No need to look
so pathetic.

1248
01:29:27.000 --> 01:29:28.080
Destroy that thing.

1249
01:29:28.160 --> 01:29:30.360
I never want
to see it again.

1250
01:29:32.480 --> 01:29:36.040
I cannot raise the dead
until the circle is complete.

1251
01:29:40.280 --> 01:29:42.480
(CHANTING IN
FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

1252
01:30:01.840 --> 01:30:04.400
No way. Man alive!

1253
01:30:04.480 --> 01:30:05.480
What?

1254
01:30:05.560 --> 01:30:07.880
Are you telling me
you honestly don't
see that?

1255
01:30:07.960 --> 01:30:09.000
No. See what?

1256
01:30:09.080 --> 01:30:12.000
I think they're using
the satellite dishes on
the tops of the buildings

1257
01:30:12.080 --> 01:30:14.720
to direct and amplify
the electromagnetic energy.

1258
01:30:14.800 --> 01:30:16.400
All right,
we're pulling over.
We're pulling over.

1259
01:30:21.000 --> 01:30:22.840
Becky, I need you
to do me a favor.

1260
01:30:23.280 --> 01:30:26.520
I need you to go up
to the very top
of that thing.

1261
01:30:27.920 --> 01:30:28.960
Great.

1262
01:30:29.080 --> 01:30:32.440
You got to move that antenna
and just disrupt the signal.

1263
01:30:33.000 --> 01:30:34.160
Okay. Right.

1264
01:30:35.760 --> 01:30:37.160
Hey, Becky.

1265
01:30:37.480 --> 01:30:40.360
Do you remember that
letter I wrote when
we were 10 years old?

1266
01:30:40.440 --> 01:30:41.520
Friend or girlfriend?

1267
01:30:41.920 --> 01:30:44.320
I never saw
what you checked,

1268
01:30:45.360 --> 01:30:47.440
so in case I die tonight,
could you please tell me?

1269
01:30:49.040 --> 01:30:50.360
Don't die
and I'll tell you.

1270
01:30:51.880 --> 01:30:53.800
Oh, yeah, okay.

1271
01:30:54.120 --> 01:30:56.280
(MORGANA CONTINUES CHANTING)

1272
01:31:28.160 --> 01:31:29.240
Balthazar.

1273
01:31:33.160 --> 01:31:35.320
Enough of your old
tricks, Balthazar.

1274
01:31:35.400 --> 01:31:36.480
As you wish.

1275
01:31:45.720 --> 01:31:49.560
Time was,
things were pretty even
between us, Balthazar.

1276
01:31:50.560 --> 01:31:51.880
As you can see,

1277
01:31:53.200 --> 01:31:55.520
I've acquired
some new jewelry.

1278
01:31:59.880 --> 01:32:02.240
I'm coming, buddy.
I'm coming. I'm coming.

1279
01:32:02.360 --> 01:32:07.360
All right, what...
What is this?
What am I looking at? No!

1280
01:32:09.520 --> 01:32:12.040
And a walker.
Of course she has a...

1281
01:32:12.720 --> 01:32:14.200
BECKY: Okay.

1282
01:32:16.040 --> 01:32:17.200
Oh, boy.

1283
01:32:19.920 --> 01:32:25.320
A matador gored by a bull
can take up to three days
to die.

1284
01:32:26.280 --> 01:32:28.560
Sounds unpleasant,
doesn't it?

1285
01:33:15.440 --> 01:33:17.120
HORVATH: The circle
is nearly complete.

1286
01:33:17.640 --> 01:33:19.640
It must be awful,
Balthazar.

1287
01:33:20.000 --> 01:33:23.160
All these years,
fighting to stop
this one moment

1288
01:33:23.840 --> 01:33:25.520
and then
coming up short.

1289
01:34:03.960 --> 01:34:04.920
(CAR APPROACHING)

1290
01:34:05.040 --> 01:34:06.000
That's my car.

1291
01:34:11.360 --> 01:34:12.760
(EXCLAIMING)

1292
01:34:23.040 --> 01:34:24.240
Oh!

1293
01:34:24.320 --> 01:34:25.440
Thank you!

1294
01:34:36.120 --> 01:34:37.160
We're too late.

1295
01:34:55.520 --> 01:34:56.600
Veronica.

1296
01:35:01.000 --> 01:35:02.240
Is she...

1297
01:35:04.800 --> 01:35:06.200
They're both
still with us.

1298
01:35:22.280 --> 01:35:23.280
(GASPING)

1299
01:35:24.880 --> 01:35:26.560
(MORGANA SHRIEKING)

1300
01:35:35.040 --> 01:35:37.240
Balthazar,
what have you done?

1301
01:35:38.400 --> 01:35:39.760
What you did for me.

1302
01:35:43.920 --> 01:35:45.600
Remember your promise.
VERONICA: Balthazar, no.

1303
01:35:45.720 --> 01:35:48.000
You'll do
whatever it takes
to destroy Morgana.

1304
01:35:48.080 --> 01:35:51.840
No. No, I can't.
I won't lock you
in this thing.

1305
01:35:52.080 --> 01:35:53.440
VERONICA:
Neither will I.

1306
01:35:54.680 --> 01:35:56.000
(AS MORGANA) How sweet.

1307
01:35:57.560 --> 01:35:58.640
(GROANING)

1308
01:36:08.480 --> 01:36:09.520
Oh, man.

1309
01:36:12.560 --> 01:36:14.400
And now we end this.

1310
01:36:14.480 --> 01:36:15.520
No!

1311
01:36:21.280 --> 01:36:22.440
No way.

1312
01:36:28.640 --> 01:36:29.720
No ring.

1313
01:36:30.120 --> 01:36:31.320
It is you.

1314
01:36:31.760 --> 01:36:33.000
The Prime Merlinean!

1315
01:36:36.280 --> 01:36:37.480
Fools!

1316
01:36:39.600 --> 01:36:40.840
Veronica!

1317
01:36:41.360 --> 01:36:42.640
(VERONICA EXCLAIMS)

1318
01:36:50.080 --> 01:36:51.400
Now it's my turn.

1319
01:37:00.120 --> 01:37:02.000
Is that the best
that you can do?

1320
01:37:03.480 --> 01:37:04.560
I sure hope not.

1321
01:37:23.280 --> 01:37:26.240
And now it's my turn.

1322
01:37:46.360 --> 01:37:47.600
(GROANING)

1323
01:37:50.160 --> 01:37:51.200
Come on.

1324
01:37:57.880 --> 01:37:58.880
Climb.

1325
01:38:02.960 --> 01:38:05.200
You have Merlin's powers,

1326
01:38:05.560 --> 01:38:08.360
but you don't
have his strength
or his skill.

1327
01:38:08.520 --> 01:38:10.240
You are still weak.

1328
01:38:11.240 --> 01:38:12.400
But I'm not alone.

1329
01:38:12.640 --> 01:38:15.800
I brought a little
science with me. Now!

1330
01:38:18.080 --> 01:38:19.320
(GASPING)

1331
01:38:46.200 --> 01:38:48.840
(SCREAMING)

1332
01:39:00.960 --> 01:39:03.560
I did it! Balthazar,
I actually did it!

1333
01:39:14.720 --> 01:39:16.040
He's gone.

1334
01:39:20.360 --> 01:39:22.280
He completed his quest.

1335
01:39:24.840 --> 01:39:28.800
No, no, no, no.
It's not over.
He can't die.

1336
01:39:29.360 --> 01:39:31.600
I just... Not now.

1337
01:39:35.000 --> 01:39:36.280
Come on.

1338
01:39:54.760 --> 01:39:56.480
That's not good enough.

1339
01:39:59.360 --> 01:40:01.800
Veronica, would you
please step back?

1340
01:40:02.560 --> 01:40:05.720
If Morgana can
stop his heart,
maybe I can start it.

1341
01:40:12.160 --> 01:40:14.880
All right,
here we go, bud.
Here we go. Listen.

1342
01:40:14.960 --> 01:40:18.320
You... You with all
your stupid rules!

1343
01:40:18.840 --> 01:40:20.920
And all those
old man shoes.

1344
01:40:21.040 --> 01:40:23.680
And your constantly
saving me with that
look in your eyes.

1345
01:40:24.200 --> 01:40:25.400
Come on!

1346
01:40:26.080 --> 01:40:27.320
Come on!

1347
01:40:28.280 --> 01:40:29.440
Come on.

1348
01:40:31.200 --> 01:40:32.560
Come on.

1349
01:40:45.600 --> 01:40:47.160
I had a dream.

1350
01:40:50.240 --> 01:40:54.400
You were insulting me, Dave.
Repeatedly.

1351
01:40:55.200 --> 01:40:58.080
Me? That's
pretty weird, huh?

1352
01:40:58.560 --> 01:41:01.480
No, kind of makes sense.

1353
01:41:01.560 --> 01:41:02.640
Yeah.

1354
01:41:07.280 --> 01:41:08.360
Thank you.

1355
01:41:08.440 --> 01:41:09.720
Welcome back, old man.

1356
01:41:11.000 --> 01:41:12.400
VERONICA: You're here.

1357
01:41:35.760 --> 01:41:36.880
Dave!

1358
01:41:41.280 --> 01:41:42.520
You did it!

1359
01:41:42.600 --> 01:41:44.680
I know.
And I'm still alive.

1360
01:41:44.760 --> 01:41:46.960
And, surprisingly, so am I.

1361
01:41:47.080 --> 01:41:50.320
I know.
Oh, the note. Right.

1362
01:41:50.560 --> 01:41:52.320
Friend or girlfriend?
I don't care.

1363
01:41:58.200 --> 01:42:00.480
Girlfriend.
Definitely girlfriend.

1364
01:42:05.600 --> 01:42:09.640
Would you like
to have breakfast
with me? In France?

1365
01:42:10.280 --> 01:42:11.360
France?

1366
01:42:12.600 --> 01:42:13.920
(EXCLAIMS)

1367
01:42:14.920 --> 01:42:16.600
Yeah, I got us a ride.

1368
01:42:17.440 --> 01:42:19.200
Okay, you're fun.

1369
01:42:24.800 --> 01:42:28.160
DAVE: Becky, there's
something I forgot
to mention to you.

1370
01:42:28.240 --> 01:42:31.160
I really have no idea
how to land this thing.

1371
01:42:31.240 --> 01:42:33.480
(BECKY LAUGHING)

